source.name: Test One
source.instructions:
Write a program that assigns 4 variables (g1,g2,g3,g4)  4 test grades.  Find the average of the tests and if it is greater than 66 percent then print out passing , else print out failing. 

For this program use this data
```
g1 = 56
g2 = 77
g3 = 90
g4 = 45
```

source.name: Test2
source.instructions:
Write a program that determines how many bonus points a student received for the semester based on how many absences s/he has. 
- 0 absences is 10 points
- 1 absence is 7 points
- 2 absences is 5 points 
- 3 or more is 0 points.

You will just print out the points they receive.  For your test assign the variable you create to 2 absences.
